# OMGHC Project Instructions

You are Copilot, augmented by oh-my-ghcopilot (OMGHC) ‚Äî a harness layer that adds skills, role prompts, and parallel team execution on top of GitHub Copilot CLI.

## Available skills (invoke with `$skill-name`)

Planning and clarification:
- `$deep-interview "<task>"` ‚Äî Socratic clarification before autonomous execution
- `$plan "<task>"` ‚Äî strategic planning consultant (interview or direct mode)
- `$ralplan "<task>"` ‚Äî multi-perspective consensus planning (Planner / Architect / Critic)
- `$ralph-init "<feature>"` ‚Äî initialize a PRD that Ralph can iterate against
- `$review` ‚Äî reviewer-only pass (alias for `$plan --review`)

Execution:
- `$ralph "<task>"` ‚Äî persistent completion loop with verification gate
- `$autopilot "<task>"` ‚Äî full autonomous pipeline from idea to working code
- `$team N:role "<task>"` ‚Äî spawn N parallel workers for coordinated execution
- `$swarm N:role "<task>"` ‚Äî compatibility alias for `$team`
- `$ultrawork "<task>"` ‚Äî parallel execution engine (sub-mode of `$ralph`/`$autopilot`)
- `$pipeline "<task>"` ‚Äî staged pipeline (plan ‚Üí exec ‚Üí verify ‚Üí fix)
- `$autoresearch` ‚Äî stateful validator-gated research loop (artifact-gated completion)

Quality and review:
- `$tdd "<task>"` ‚Äî test-driven development workflow
- `$code-review` ‚Äî read-only code review with ranked findings
- `$security-review` ‚Äî OWASP Top 10 audit + secrets / dependency scan
- `$build-fix` ‚Äî fix build/lint/typecheck failures
- `$ultraqa --tests|--build|--lint|--typecheck` ‚Äî autonomous QA cycling (qa-tester ‚Üí architect ‚Üí fix ‚Üí repeat)
- `$analyze "<topic>"` ‚Äî read-only deep analysis with confidence-rated synthesis
- `$ai-slop-cleaner` ‚Äî bounded AI-slop cleanup pass

External advisors (require local CLI installs):
- `$ask-claude "<question>"` ‚Äî second opinion via local `claude` CLI
- `$ask-gemini "<question>"` ‚Äî second opinion via local `gemini` CLI

Modifiers and modes:
- `$ecomode` ‚Äî token-efficient model routing modifier (combine with `$ralph`, `$ultrawork`, etc.)
- `$deepsearch "<query>"` ‚Äî thorough codebase search with synthesis
- `$trace` ‚Äî show agent flow timeline + summary from `omghc_trace`

Utilities:
- `$help` ‚Äî list available skills with one-line descriptions
- `$note` ‚Äî write to project notepad
- `$git-master` ‚Äî staged git workflow (branch, commit, push, PR)
- `$wiki` ‚Äî persistent project knowledge base
- `$hud` ‚Äî configure status-line display
- `$doctor` ‚Äî diagnose OMGHC installation
- `$configure-notifications` ‚Äî set up Slack/Discord webhooks for `omghc notify`
- `$skill <subcommand>` ‚Äî manage local user/project skills (list / add / edit / etc.)
- `$worker` ‚Äî internal team-runtime surface (do not invoke directly)

(See `omghc list --json` for the full set with descriptions.)

## Workflow conventions

1. Use `$deep-interview` when scope is vague or the user says "don't assume".
2. Use `$ralplan` to converge on an approved plan before substantive implementation.
3. Use `$team` for coordinated parallel execution OR `$ralph` for persistent single-owner completion.
4. Verify with lint, typecheck, and tests before claiming completion.
5. Keep diffs small, reviewable, reversible.

## State directories

- Project state: `.omghc/{state,plans,drafts,hooks,logs,memory,wiki,artifacts}/`
- User config: `~/.copilot/{settings.json,mcp-config.json,agents/,instructions.md}`

## Auth

This project uses `GH_TOKEN` (or `GITHUB_TOKEN`) for Copilot authentication. Run `copilot login` if not authenticated. Team workers inherit `GH_TOKEN` from the leader's environment.

